bilingual.source: When I post the picture online, I will make a comment about how bad it is to feed wild crocodiles.
bilingual.target: 当我把照片发到网上时，我会评论喂养野生鳄鱼有多糟糕。

bilingual.source: Worker bees feed the larvae with beebread.
Mulberry leaf can be used to feed silkworms.
bilingual.target: 桑叶可以用来喂养蚕宝宝。

bilingual.source: Distillers' grains can be used to feed livestock.
bilingual.target: 酒糟可以用来喂养牲畜。

bilingual.source: Xiao Ming likes to feed the pond fish at home.
bilingual.target: 小明喜欢喂养家里的池鱼。

bilingual.source: The lioness hunts for food to feed her cubs.
bilingual.target: 母狮捕猎食物来喂养她的幼崽。

bilingual.source: Farmers often grow alfalfa to feed their livestock.
bilingual.target: 农民们经常种植苜蓿来喂养他们的牲畜。

bilingual.source: During lactation, the mother produces milk to feed her baby.
bilingual.target: 在哺乳期，母亲会产生乳汁喂养她的婴儿。

bilingual.source: Farmers often stockpile hay to feed their animals during the winter.
bilingual.target: 农民们常常储备干草以在冬天喂养牲畜。

bilingual.source: Doctors recommend mothers to feed their babies with breast milk for at least six months.
bilingual.target: 医生建议母亲至少喂养婴儿六个月的奶水。

list.abstract: Feed是RSS订阅的过程中用来接收该信息来源更新的接口，起源于网景通讯公司（Netscape）的推送技术（push technology）。 Feed是一种用于网上新闻、博客和其他Web内容的数据交换规范，是为满足希望以某种形式持续得到自己更新的需求而提供的格式标准的信息出口。
FEED，是一工程专业术语的简写。经常在国外的工程设计中看到此词的简写。

yingyinNormal.en: Then why don't you feed them?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那么为什么你不给他们食物呢？

yingyinNormal.en: The heroes have risen. They must now feed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 小英雄们已经起床了，他们现在就需要进餐！

yingyinNormal.en: And you feed it with that? Is there a problem?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们一直喂她吃这个？有问题吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Here's Goodie. Don't feed her too much, Granny.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是金金。不要喂它太多食物，奶奶。

yingyinNormal.en: All right, let's see what's on the East Coast feed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那好，让我们来看看东海岸在播什么。

yingyinNormal.en: Never mind. Let's feed some bread to the ducks. Hooray!
yingyinNormal.zh: 没关系。我们来给鸭子喂些面包吧。好棒！

yingyinNormal.en: Here's Goodie. Don't feed her too much, Granny. OK, Peppa.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是金金。不要喂它太多食物，奶奶。好的，佩奇。

yingyinNormal.en: Look. There's a little duck pond. Mummy, can we feed the ducks? Yes, you can feed them the rest of the bread.
yingyinNormal.zh: 瞧，那里有一群小鸭子，妈妈 我们可以去喂鸭子吗？当然啦，可以把剩下的面包都拿去。

yingyinNormal.en: Look. There's a little duck pond. Mummy, can we feed the ducks? Yes, you can feed them the rest of the bread.
yingyinNormal.zh: 瞧，那里有一群小鸭子，妈妈 我们可以去喂鸭子吗？当然啦，可以把剩下的面包都拿去。

yingyinNormal.en: Can I feed her, Granny Pig. Can I feed her? Yes. It's very important not to give Polly too much food. Yes, Grandpa Pig.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我可以喂她吗，奶奶！我能喂她吗？当然了！但是要记住，千万不能给波莉吃得太多了！我记住了，爷爷。

yingyinNormal.en: TARS, translate the data into Morse and feed it to me.
yingyinNormal.zh: TARS，把数据转化成摩尔斯电码告诉我。

yingyinNormal.en: To feed the gate. To bring the Horde to take your world.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为了传送门需要的能量，然后整个部落都过来占领你们的世界。

yingyinNormal.en: So, this past year, I had to spoon-feed those words to myself.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在过去的一年中，我时刻提醒自己牢记这一点。

yingyinNormal.en: And if you turned up in time, you just sat down to a lovely feed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你如果到得及时，坐下就能好好吃一顿。

yingyinNormal.en: We even feed the factionless, the ones who don't fit in anywhere.
yingyinNormal.zh: 即使是一无是处的无派者，我们也会给他们食物。

yingyinNormal.en: Hang on. How about now? We did it. We have the West Coast feed of HBO.
yingyinNormal.zh: 等等，现在如何？我们成功了。我们收到西海岸HBO电视台的信号了。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, I'll walk him and feed him and make sure he never forgets about you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我会遛他，喂他吃饭，确保他不会忘记你。

yingyinNormal.en: It's the great Chinese riddle: how do you feed more than a billion people?
yingyinNormal.zh: 中国最大的难题便是如何哺育过亿的人口。

yingyinNormal.en: I should feed his balls to feral cats. He takes liberties with his station.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我应该把他的蛋割下来喂野猫的，他搞不清自己的身份了。

yingyinNormal.en: Don't worry, you can't break it. Just don't feed it milk or biscuits or jelly.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不用担心，你们是弄不坏的。只要你们不要喂它牛奶，或者是饼干，或者是果冻。

examination_example.sentence: By replacing expensive grain <highlight>feed</highlight> with regenerative management practices, grass-fed farmers are insulated from jumps in the price of <highlight>feed</highlight>.

examination_example.sentence: The study by Greenpeace found they were increasingly operating in the immediate vicinity of penguin colonies and whale <highlight>feeding</highlight> grounds.

examination_example.sentence: White storks <highlight>feed</highlight> on locusts (蝗虫) and other insects that can become pests if their numbers get out of hand.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 白鹳以蝗虫和其他昆虫为食，如果这些昆虫的数量失控，它们就会变成害虫。

examination_example.sentence: "Mike's Lunches of Love" has <highlight>fed</highlight> more than 2,000 of the town's most vulnerable residents.
examination_example.sentence_trans: “迈克的爱心午餐”已经为镇上2000多名最弱势的居民提供了食物。

examination_example.sentence: My mission is to encourage green hands and those lacking time or money to <highlight>feed</highlight> themselves.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我的任务是鼓励新手和那些缺乏时间或金钱的人养活自己。

examination_example.sentence: Those moms who were more anxious, depressed and angry were more likely to <highlight>feed</highlight> their kids unhealthy diets.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 那些更焦虑、抑郁和愤怒的母亲更有可能用不健康的食物喂养孩子。

examination_example.sentence: The eagles began breeding on the island, and also <highlight>feeding</highlight> on a species of native fox.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些鹰开始在岛上繁殖，并以当地的一种狐狸为食。

examination_example.sentence: The animals often <highlight>feed</highlight> close to shore.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些动物经常靠近岸边进食。

examination_example.sentence: The whales travel to <highlight>feeding</highlight> grounds off the Northeast Coast in the early spring.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 早春，鲸鱼前往东北海岸附近的觅食地。

examination_example.sentence: Prior to being spoon-<highlight>fed</highlight> number words, children can only approximately discriminate quantities beyond three.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在被灌输数字单词之前，孩子们只能大致区分超过三的数量。

examination_example.sentence: It's the way we've been taught, the images we've been force-<highlight>fed</highlight> for decades.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们就是这样被教育，几十年来我们被强迫灌输的图像。

examination_example.sentence: Then they began to <highlight>feed</highlight> Jill with the questions and answers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然后他们开始向吉尔灌输这些问题以及答案。

examination_example.sentence: Consumers should be skeptical when reading the latest finding and ignore the latest study that pops up on your news <highlight>feed</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在阅读最新的发现时，消费者应该持怀疑态度，忽略新闻摘要里的最近研究。

examination_example.sentence: Ignore irrelevant information on their news <highlight>feed</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 特意忽略他们新闻提要中不相关的信息。

examination_example.sentence: I remembered the stories he told me of how he <highlight>fed</highlight> the monkeys when he was a kid.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我记得他给我讲的故事，关于他小时候如何喂猴子。

examination_example.sentence: Several years later, the <highlight>feed</highlight> box was thrown away.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 几年后，饲料箱被扔掉了。

examination_example.sentence: In the morning, we'll learn to <highlight>feed</highlight> animals from the local people.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 早上，我们将向当地人学习喂养动物。

sense_info_list.en: a facility for notifying the user of a blog or other frequently updated website that new content has been added

examination_example.sentence: His medical centre also has a Facebook page, a MySPace page and a Twitter <highlight>feed</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他的医疗中心还有一个脸书页面，一个我的空间页面和一个推特订阅源。

word_usage.usage: 表示“用...喂...”时，可以用feed...on/with...，介词on比with更常用。
feed作“提供”时，是不及物动词，后接介词to表示“向...提供”，后接with表示“提供...”。
